@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction to Ejecter"
    I wrote because the button on the front of my CD Drive is very small and
    doesn't work sometimes so I wrote the original version of this program which
    was just a simple button in a window.
@ENDNODE
@NODE FEATURES "The features of Ejecter"
    * Uses Gadtools
    * Supports Newicons and MagicWB
    * Very configurable with tooltypes
    * Runs as a commodity
@ENDNODE
@NODE INSTALLATION "How to Install Ejecter"
    You can either run it from a directory or put it in WBStartup.
@ENDNODE
@NODE USAGE "How use Ejecter"
    The program itself is very easy to use.  It is just a window with a button
    itside of it.  You can configure Ejecter with use of the tooltypes in
    the icon.

    @{i}The tooltypes@{ui}

    @{b}Device@{ub}
    This is your CD drive device which is needed by Ejecter to run correctly.  You
    are required to change it to the CD device you use and you are also required
    to add the ".device" to the end of the the name. Eg

      Atapi.device

    Default it CD.device


    @{b}Unit@{ub}
    This is also required by Ejecter to run correctly.	It is the Unit number of your
    CD drive.  Eg

      3

    Default is 0


    @{b}WINX@{ub}
    This sets the x (left) co-ordinates of the window to the number is.  Default is 0.


    @{b}WINY@{ub}
    This sets the y (top) co-ordinates of the window to the number is.  Default is 0.


    @{b}WINW@{ub}
    This sets the width of the window to the number.  Default is 100.


    @{b}WINH@{ub}
    This sets the height of the window to the number.  Default is 30.


    @{b}WINTITLE@{ub}
    This sets the title of the window to the text.  Default is "".


    @{b}CENTRE@{ub} @{b}@{i}(YES|NO)@{ub}@{ui}
    This overwrites the WINX and WINY co-ordinates and puts the window in the centre of
    the screen.  Default is NO.


    @{b}FONTNAME@{ub}
    This changes the button font to the chosen font.  You have to add the ".font" to
    the end. eg

    XEN.font

    Default is Ejecter.font


    @{b}FONTHEIGHT@{ub}
    This changes the fontheight to the number.	Eg

    12

    Default is 9

    @{b}BUTTONTEXT@{ub}
    This changes the Text in the button to the text.  Default is a (the Eject button).


    @{b}CX_POPUP@{ub} @{b}@{i}(YES|NO)@{ub}@{ui}
    This decides whether you want to open the window when you load the program.

@ENDNODE
